	(text "The regulator is capable of sourcing\n2 A @ V_{IN} = 3 V and 4 A @ V_{IN} = 5V.\n\nThe MCU draws approximately 100 mA in the worst-case scenario.\nThe modem draws approximately 500 mA in the worst-case scenario.\n\nThe values for the inductor and the feedback resistors are generated\nby the Texas Instruments' WEBENCH Power Designer tool with\nthe following parameters:\n- V_{IN}_MIN = 3.0 V\n- V_{IN}_MAX = 5.0 V\n- V_{OUT} = 3.3 V\n- I_{OUT}_MAX = 2 A"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 178.308 117.094 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "1cd74119-79b0-4b56-a21d-126ceaed6e5d")
	)
	(text "Testing: Power-saving mode should be enabled\nbut if it doesn't work,\nprovide an easy way to disable it."
